assessment_details.task_description:
Mode: Individual essay (2500 words + reference list)

Airbnb is a website for people to rent lodgings. Founded in August 2008 and headquartered in San Francisco, California, the company has over 800,000 listings in 33,000 cities and 192 countries. Airbnb has usurped the InterContinental Hotels Group and Hilton Worldwide as the world's largest hotel chain—without owning a single hotel. The new entrants to the hospitality industry, such as Airbnb and others, have reshaped the hotel business model and value chain. As Frank Kermarrec (Director of Commercial and Brand Portfolio Strategy at IHG) said, “ the hotel industry will change dramatically. This is why Airbnb is a real chance for those big hotel corporations: it will force them to think, work and sell differently. Airbnb will force them to move from being only a good professional to becoming a great hotelier .”

Based on this background context, you are required to write an essay that:

describes the nature and characteristics of airbnb;

analyses the fast development of airbnb - both the demand and supply perspectives must be addressed;

critically discusses the negative and positive impacts of airbnb on traditional 4 or 5 star hotels;

explores and recommends what traditional 4 or 5 star hotels can learn from airbnb.

Referencing: Referencing style for this assessment item is APA6.

Format: 1.5 line spacing, 12 point, Times New Roman/Arial
